      • findElementByIdAndSubstring

        public boolean findElementByIdAndSubstring​(java.lang.String id,
                                           java.lang.String text)
        Definition: This method verify if a component with id and text informed exist

        Scenery: It necessary verify if a Label or TextField 'Login' component, exist on the screen

        Use tip: Boolean existComponent = findElementByIdAndSubstring("login_component_ID", "Type login");

        Expected result: TRUE or FALSE

        Parameters:
        id - component's verified on the source code
        text - expected in the component. Example: "Type login"
        Returns:
        Boolean TRUE or FALSE
        Since:
        2020/03/01
